johne@cernvm.cern.ch, thank you)This paper is based on lectures presented to mathematical physicists andattempts to provide an overview of the present status of the Standard Model,its experimental tests, phenomenological and experimental motivations for goingbeyond the Standard Model via supersymmetry and grand unification, and ways totest these ideas with particle accelerators.